ithonline\/2010\/10\/18\/warning-torment-animals\/","url_meta":{"origin":23969,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Cruelty: Severe punishment for torturing animals","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 18, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cA woman was punished due to a cat she had imprisoned until it died, so she entered the Hellfire. She did not give it food or water while it was imprisoned, nor did she set it\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25563,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/06\/muslim-brother-another-muslim\/","url_meta":{"origin":23969,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Brotherhood: The Muslim is a brother to another Muslim","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 6, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe Muslim is the brother of another Muslim. He does not wrong him, nor surrender him. Whoever fulfills the needs of his brother, Allah will fulfill his needs. Whoever relieves a Muslim from distress, Allah\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11839,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/25\/permission-to-keep-gifts\/","url_meta":{"origin":23969,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Gifts: Take gifts to keep or give away in charity","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 25, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, gave me a gift and I said, \"Give it to someone poorer than me.\" The Prophet said, \"Take it and keep it or give it in charity. Whatever comes to you of this property, take it without extravagance\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15168,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/21\/prophet-shrouded-janazah\/","url_meta":{"origin":23969,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Janazah: The Prophet shrouded for his funeral","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 21, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was shrouded for his funeral in three white cotton garments, among which was neither a shirt, nor a turban. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1264, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 941 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15542,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/05\/zakat-minimum-amounts\/","url_meta":{"origin":23969,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Zakat: No charity is due on minimum amounts","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 5, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u